30 deadline and intensify their role.
UN and international observers attended the meeting.
Mr Jonas Savimbi, Unita leader, rejected as rigged the results of Angola's
first multi-party general election in September, in which the ruling MPLA
party won 129 of the new parliament's 220 seats.
President Jose Eduardo dos Santos won the presidential election but narrowly
failed to gain the absolute majority he needed to avoid a run-off with Mr
Savimbi.
