FT  27 NOV 92 / Women 'find new jobs more quickly'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LISA WOOD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
WOMEN executives find new jobs more quickly than men after being made
redundant or being fired, according to InterExec, the career management and
outplacement consultants, Lisa Wood writes.
A survey of the company's clients says men in the Pounds 30,000-Pounds
40,000 salary range took more than six months to get a new job while women
in the same bracket took just over three months.
The results are endorsed by DBM, another outplacement consultancy, which
said the most likely explanation was that women have to work harder to
become executives and therefore they are the better qualified when it comes
to making new job applications.
Consultants said, however, that men are better at networking among contacts
to find new jobs.
