policy-making core' with independent organisations delivering services.
He said the National Health Service was benefiting from reforms separating
the purchasers of services from their providers, and said he aimed to
establish the same system throughout public service.
Mr Waldegrave accepted that there should be a level playing field between
'in-house' bids and those made by private contractors.
Inland Revenue typists and secretaries yesterday lobbied parliament to
protest at the alleged threat to taxpayers' confidentiality in plans to
privatise their work.
