<HEADLINE>
FT  27 NOV 92 / Economy may be expanding
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
AN INDICATION that demand in the economy may be expanding has come with the
latest figures for the volume of banknotes in circulation, released
yesterday by the Bank of England.
They indicate that M0, the narrow measure of the money supply which is a
good guide to overall demand, has risen this month by about 3 per cent
compared with November last year. If confirmed when the Bank issues official
M0 figures on December 18, that would be the biggest year-on-year rise for
M0 in any month this year.
