FT  27 NOV 92 / UK Company News: Phil Harris plans listing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MAGGIE URRY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SIR PHIL HARRIS, who sold the Harris Queensway furniture and carpet group in
1988 and then saw it go into receivership, is planning to take his
Carpetright retail chain public next year, he said yesterday.
He received about Pounds 70m for his shares in Harris Queensway when it was
taken over for Pounds 450m. He then set up the Carpetright chain, with some
backing from MFI Furniture Group, which still has a 22 per cent stake. Mr
Derek Hunt, chairman of MFI, is also head of Carpetright, which rents 18
stores from MFI.
Sir Phil was speaking at the annual meeting of Great Universal Stores, the
retail and finance group, where he is a non-executive director.
Lord Wolfson, chairman of GUS, told his shareholders that profits for the
half year to end-September were ahead of the comparable period last year.
Then they were Pounds 186.6m.
Asked by a shareholder about possible enfranchisement of the non-voting
shares, Lord Wolfson said the matter was being kept under review.
