rose to Dollars 180m in the latest quarter from Dollars 165.6m.
In October, the Standard &amp; Poor's ratings agency lowered its rating on
Carolco's senior debt to double C and kept the ratings on credit watch,
reflecting the company's continuing debt and liquidity pressures.
For the first nine months, Carolco had a net loss of Dollars 51.9m, or
Dollars 1.90.
