sheep and Mr Evans said that Welsh lamb deserved its quality premium.
Lamb exports, especially to France, Spain and Italy, were rising
satisfactorily and had gone up by a third in the past two months alone. This
was before French farmers had threatened to dent the trade. A blockade
against British imports this weekend is threatened as part of their
opposition to the agreement on farm products just concluded between the
European Commission and the US on farm products.
