<HEADLINE>
FT  26 NOV 92 / UK Company News: Chester Waterworks achieves Pounds 1.04m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Chester Waterworks Company, the statutory water company which acts as agent
for the Welsh Water Authority and the North West Water Authority, reported
pre-tax profits of Pounds 1.04m for the six months to September 30.
The company has changed its year end, and for the 15-month period ended
March 31 profits were Pounds 2.45m. Turnover amounted to Pounds 2.86m
(Pounds 6.58m).
Mr Joseph Musgrave, the chairman, said the results were being published in
anticipation of proposed changes in the company's constitution, including
re-registration as a plc.
Pro forma earnings per share were 283p (655p) and the dividend 2.1p, the
maximum statutory rate. An interim dividend of 75p is forecast, subject to
the removal of the statutory restrictions in the new year.
